:<!--Trigger PerformanceE 200010113: Config/Level/Mission/2000101/Act/Act200010113.json-->
:'''Hinkel:''' {{MC|f=Young lady|m=Young man}}, you're back. Let me concentrate and inspect your work.
:'''Hinkel:''' There is a 0.5 ms time delay between the sound reaching both ears, which indicates that the source is in the 3 or 9 o'clock position.
:'''Hinkel:''' The sound is much louder in the left ear, which confirms the 9 o'clock position. That means the monsters in the 3 o'clock position have been eliminated. Good job.
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} Such an incredible skill!
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_200022333-->
::'''Hinkel:''' It's just sonar positioning. Nothing to brag about.
::'''Hinkel:''' In the Herta Department of Ecology, we deal with all sorts of cosmic creatures every day. Developing this kind of ability is just part of our training.
::'''Hinkel:''' The staff of Herta Space Station possess many different abilities. After meeting a few of us, you won't be surprised anymore.
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} I can't hear anything.
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_200022337-->
::'''Hinkel:''' You're untrained. It's normal that you can't hear anything. This is a sonar positioning technique that is unique to the space station's Ecology staff.
::'''Hinkel:''' In the Herta Department of Ecology, we deal with all sorts of cosmic creatures every day. Developing this kind of ability is just part of our training.
::'''Hinkel:''' The staff of Herta Space Station possess many different abilities. After meeting a few of us, you won't be surprised anymore.
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} Why don't you just take a look...
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_200022341-->
::'''Hinkel:''' Hehe, you have a point.
::'''Hinkel:''' I should also reflect on whether I, like so many others, have fallen into the trap of overreliance on Erudition and disregarding the much simpler and perhaps more effective methods.
:'''Hinkel:''' In short, thank you for your contribution to Herta Space Station. This is the reward I managed to secure for you from Lead Researcher Asta. Please take it.
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} Thank you. You seem to care a lot about this place.
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_200022345-->
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} No need to reward me for such a minor good deed.
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_200022346-->
::'''Hinkel:''' I disagree. All these minor acts of kindness are precisely what make the reconstruction possible.
:'''Hinkel:''' Back when I was an unknown researcher, I was told by the first group of people who worked on the construction of Herta Space Station, "This universe is never friendly. Rather, it is vast and dark."
:'''Hinkel:''' In this vast universe, there are countless pairs of eyes staring at the space station, with various intentions.
:'''Hinkel:''' Some covet its Curios, while others envy its neutrality and freedom.
:'''Hinkel:''' Others despise it or see it as a chess piece that can be destroyed and trampled on at will.
:'''Hinkel:''' Perhaps we researchers are the only ones who understand the joy, sadness, epiphany, and companionship that it has brought us.
:'''Hinkel:''' Which is why it is up to us to give everything we have to protect it.
:<!--Ends the current performance-->
:<!--Custom String Trigger: Mission_200010113-->
